\details{
The two overridden private seams are:
\itemize{
\item \code{.sign()} — Census authentication is a single query-parameter \code{key}, so this
appends \verb{&key=<CENSUS_API_KEY>} to the request (via the internal
\code{census_sign_key()}). There is no HMAC or JWT; the timestamp context is
unused.
\item \code{.parse_envelope()} — the Census envelope (via the internal
\code{parse_census_response()}): it detects the missing/invalid-key HTML page
(which arrives as an HTTP 200 because \code{httr2} follows the redirect), the
\code{text/plain} API error bodies, and the empty-body no-data case, and otherwise
parses the array-of-arrays.
