\subsection{Sync vs async}{

The \code{async} argument selects the execution mode for every method:
\itemize{
\item \code{async = FALSE} (default): methods return a \link[data.table:data.table]{data.table::data.table}.
\item \code{async = TRUE}: methods return a \link[promises:promise]{promises::promise} that resolves to the
same \code{data.table}.
}

The mode is stored once as \code{private$.is_async} and threaded through every
method's \code{connectcore::then_or_now(res, ..., is_async = private$.is_async)}
tail; nothing hardcodes it. Consume promises with \code{\link[coro:async]{coro::async()}} and \code{await()};
drive the loop in a script with \code{while (!later::loop_empty()) later::run_now()}.
}

\subsection{The API key}{

The key is read from the \code{CENSUS_API_KEY} environment variable (the \code{api_key}
argument overrides). An empty key \strong{warns} at construction rather than
aborting -- so a caller can still introspect metadata -- and a data query with
an empty (or invalid) key aborts with a typed \link{census_conditions} error at
request time.

This class is not meant to be instantiated directly; subclasses (e.g.
\link{CensusEconomicIndicators}) define the public methods.
